claims:
Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. A guidewire managing assembly for determining the location of a medical device in a subject during a procedure, the assembly comprising a means for attaching the guidewire managing assembly to an instrument, an entry port for a guidewire, a means for measuring one or more lengths of a guidewire or section thereof, a mechanism for locking the measuring means, a means for determining measured values and calculating distances, and a means for transmitting one or more values and distances to a separate component. 2. The assembly of claim 1 wherein the instrument is a catheter handle. 3. The assembly of claim 2 wherein the attachment means on the catheter handle is a luer-lock port. 4. The assembly of claim 3 wherein the means for attaching the guidewire managing assembly is a luer-lock tip. 5. The assembly of claim 4 further including a catheter shaft. 6. The assembly of claim 1 further including a display. 7. The assembly of claim 1 wherein the means for measuring one or more lengths of a guidewire or section thereof includes a means selected from the group consisting of a measuring wheel, an optical detector, and combinations thereof. 8. The assembly of claim 1 wherein the means for transmitting one or more values and distances to a separate component comprises a wireless transmitter. 9. A method of tracking a catheter tip inside the body of a subject, the method comprising: zeroing a guidewire managing assembly using a medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire; 

 recording a length of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire at which the guidewire is aligned with a tip of a catheter shaft; recording a total length of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire; introducing the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire into a target vessel in the body of a patient and monitoring and recording its position and location during introduction to derive a vessel profile; introducing the catheter shaft over the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire and into the target vessel; and estimating the location of the tip of the catheter shaft in the vessel using the guidewire managing assembly and the location of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire. 10. The method of claim 9 wherein the recording a length of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire at which the guidewire is aligned with a tip of a catheter shaft is done using the guidewire managing assembly. 11. The method of claim 9 wherein the recording a total length of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire is done using the guidewire managing assembly. 12. The method of claim 9 further including providing a therapy to the subject using the catheter. 13. The method of claim 9 wherein the estimating is done by the guidewire managing assembly communicating with a separate processing component. 14. The method of claim 9 wherein the guidewire managing assembly comprises a means for attaching the guidewire managing assembly to a device, an entry port for a guidewire, a means of measuring one or more lengths of a guidewire or section thereof, a mechanism for locking the measuring means, a means of 

 determining measured values and calculating distances, and a means of transmitting one or more values and distances to a separate component. 15. A system for determining the location of a catheter tip in a subject during a procedure, the system comprising a medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire, a catheter handle attached to a catheter shaft, and a guidewire managing assembly attached to the catheter handle, the guidewire managing assembly comprising an entry port for the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire, a means for measuring one or more lengths of the medical positioning system sensor enabled guidewire or section thereof, a mechanism for locking the measuring means, a means for determining measured values and calculating distances, and a means for transmitting one or more values and distances to a separate component.
